Incident Response > [T3]: Lab - Sysmon: Configuration overview

Overview of Sysmon configuration

Sysmon is pre-installed in your lab machine, and by default, it logs the events in EventLog.

To see the logs open your cmd and execute the eventvwr command, then head to Applications and Services Logs => Microsoft => Windows => Sysmon => Operational.

 

Sysmon configuration is defined in XML format. To create a configuration file, you need to specify the Sysmon schema version and use a specific structure that will be explained later on.


The first line in the above screenshot has to have the schemaversion attribute, which will keep changing whenever Sysmon gets a new update or feature.

You can only have one single EventType per RuleGroup. Sysmon will not error if you have more than one, but only the first EventType filters will be loaded.

In the above screenshot, you must write XML attributes correctly for the rule to be effectively triggered.

  • groupRelation attribute has to be either and or or
  • EventType onmatch attribute has to be either include or exclude
  • You should set the condition to one of the following conditions: is, is not, contains, contains any, is any, contains all, excludes, excludes any, excludes all, begin with, not begin with, end with, not end with, less than, more than, image.

 

That might look complicated but bear with us. We will explain this when writing our own logging rule.
